==Serbian==
===Etymology===
A compound of [[med#Serbian|med]] (''honey'') and Old Slavic '''ved''' or '''ued''' (which can also be rendered as '''vjed''' or '''ujed''') (''eater'').  So literally, '''honey-eater'''.

